  "prompt": "I've scored a 77 percentile in the CAT 2014. It's my first attempt, and I have 1.5 years of work experience as of now. Should I reappear again for the CAT 2015?",
  "response": "Here are some factors to consider:\n\nPros of Reappearing:\n1. 77 percentile is decent but not exceptional for top B-schools\n2. More time to prepare and improve your score\n3. With 1.5-2 years work experience, you'll have a stronger profile\n4. You now understand the exam pattern and can strategize better\n5. Potential for significant score improvement\n\nCons of Reappearing:\n1. Time and effort required for preparation\n2. Risk of not improving significantly\n3. Opportunity cost of dedicated preparation time\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Analyze your previous CAT performance\n- Identify weak sections\n- Understand why you scored 77 percentile\n- Assess potential for improvement\n\n2. Check target B-schools' cutoffs\n- Many top schools require 80+ percentile\n- Some accept 75-80 percentile with strong work experience\n\n3. Preparation Strategy\n- Take mock tests\n- Focus on weak areas\n- Consider coaching/guidance\n- Practice consistently\n\n4. Alternative Options\n- Consider other entrance exams (XAT, NMAT)\n- Look at MBA programs with lower percentile requirements\n\nFinal Advice: If you're committed and can significantly improve, reappear for CAT 2015.",
